    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-21T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-21T20:00:00-05:00" n="370"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d370">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115/616: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jarvis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-21T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 21, 1939—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. Your 93, April 19, 5 p.m.<note n="52" xml:id="d370fn52">Not printed; it
                        reported that Americans were planning to depart aboard American gunboats
                        without Japanese “permission” (393.115/615).</note> The Department assumes
                    from your telegram that you do not anticipate any physical attempt to prevent
                    departure from Hankow of Americans who have not obtained Japanese “permission”.
                    The Department also assumes that any Americans who may leave Hankow without such
                    “permission” and who may decide to return to Hankow have in mind the practical
                    difficulties that might attend their return landing or sojourn.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Chungking, Peiping, and Shanghai.</p>
                <p>Shanghai please repeat to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
